03/12/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Organised crimes prosecutors announced on Thursday (December 2nd) they have pressed charges against Milenko Sarancic, former head of Serbian Railways, and three other former officials accused of abuse of office.
Sarancic was arrested in June over a 2004 deal to buy six diesel engines from Slovenia and Sweden, resulting in damages to the company's budget totalling 1.2m euros.
(B92, Tanjug, Vecernje Novosti, Press Online, Blic, Kurir - 02/12/10)
